recards/79/79751.html 159]\n|28 June 2004\n|Oxford\n|style=\"background:#004685; color:#FFFFFF\"|Oxford\n|innings and 77 runs\n|<small>[[Joe Sayers (cricketer)|JJ Sayers]] 147, DR Fox 104 and PJ McMahon 99 for Oxford<br>completed in three days</small>\n|-\n|[http://www.espncricinfo.com/series/18213/scorecard/212206/cambridge-university-vs-oxford-university--university-match-2005/ 160]\n|28 June 2005\n|Cambridge\n|style=\"background:#004685; color:#FFFFFF\"|Oxford\n|innings and 213 runs\n|<small>Oxford 610-5dec, ;<br>[[Salil Oberoi|S Oberoi]] 247 for Oxford, to date the highest individual score in the series;<br>Oberoi and DR Fox (184) put on 408 for the third wicket, the highest partnership in the fixture</small>\n|-\n|[https://cricketarchive.com/Archive/Scorecards/86/86196.html 161]\n|3 July 2006\n|Oxford\n|style=\"background:#004685; color:#FFFFFF\"|Oxford\n|9 wickets\n|<small>[[Salil Oberoi|S Oberoi]] 115 and [[Michael Munday|MK Munday]] 6-77 & 5-66 for Oxford\n|-\n|[http://www.espncricinfo.com/series/18193/scorecard/292466/cambridge-university-vs-oxford-university-varsity-match-university-match-2007/ 162]\n|30 June 2007\n|Cambridge\n|bgcolor=\"#FFEBAD\"|Drawn\n|\n|\n|-\n|[http://www.espncricinfo.com/series/18176/scorecard/334083/oxford-university-vs-cambridge-university-varsity-match-university-match-2008/ 163]\n|1 July 2008\n|Oxford\n|bgcolor=\"#FFEBAD\"|Drawn\n|\n|<small>AS Ansari 193 & 80 not out and 4-50 (1st inns) and NMH Whittington 83 (1st inns) for Cambridge<br>EJ Morse 6-102 (1st inns) and N Kruger 172 for Oxford</small>\n|-\n|[http://www.espncricinfo.com/series/18163/scorecard/395689/cambridge-university-vs-oxford-university-varsity-match-university-match-2009/ 164]\n|7 July 2009\n|Cambridge\n|style=\"background:#B7E1E4\"|Cambridge\n|10 wickets\n|<small>AS Ansari 132 (1st inns) and RMR Braithwaite 8-130 for Cambridge<br>N Kruger 98 (2nd inns) and R Sharma 5-96 for Oxford</small>\n|-\n|[http://www.espncricinfo.com/series/18151/scorecard/444073/oxford-university-vs-cambridge-university-varsity-match-university-match-2010/ 165]\n|6 July 2010\n|Oxford\n|style=\"background:#004685; color:#FFFFFF\"|Oxford\n|innings and 28 runs\n|<small>DA King 189 (1st inns), SS Agarwal 117 (1st inns) & 5-78 (2nd inns), AS Sharma 189* (1st inns), DC Pascoe 5-38 (1st inns) and AJD Scott 8-147 (both inns) for Oxford<br>[[Phil Hughes (cricketer, born 1991)|PH Hughes]] 74 & 87, A Ashok 93 (2nd inns) for Cambridge</small>\n|-\n|[http://www.espncricinfo.com/series/18142/scorecard/500233/cambridge-university-vs-oxford-university-varsity-match-university-match-2011/ 166]\n|5 July 2011\n|Cambridge\n|style=\"background:#B7E1E4\"|Cambridge\n|56 runs\n|<small>PM Best 6-86 (2nd inns), ADJ Kennedy 5 dismissals (2nd inngs) for Cambridge<br>R Sharma 114 (2nd inns) for Oxford</small>\n|-\n|[http://www.espncricinfo.com/series/18131/scorecard/553792/oxford-university-vs-cambridge-university-varsity-match-university-match-2012/ 167]\n|24 June 2012\n|Oxford\n|bgcolor=\"#FFEBAD\"|Drawn\n|\n|<small> </small>\n|-\n|[http://www.espncricinfo.com/series/18121/scorecard/601764/cambridge-university-vs-oxford-university-varsity-match-university-match-2013/ 168]\n|2 July 2013\n|Cambridge\n|style=\"background:#004685; color:#FFFFFF\"|Oxford\n|innings and 186 runs\n|<small>[[Sam Agarwal|SS Agarwal]] 313* (1st inns), [[Tom Williams (cricketer)|TJ Williams]] 5-34 (1st inns) and 8-69 (match), [[Sachin Mylavarapu|SVS Mylavarapu]] 5-23 (1st inns) and 8-110 (match) for Oxford<br>[[Phil Hughes (cricketer, born 1991)|PH Hughes]] 92 (2nd inns), TC Elliott 101 (2nd inns) for Cambridge<br>completed in three days</small>\n|-\n|[http://www.espncricinfo.com/series/18113/scorecard/715339/oxford-university-vs-cambridge-university-varsity-match-university-match-2014/ 169]\n|30 June 2014\n|Oxford\n|bgcolor=\"#FFEBAD\"|Drawn\n|\n|<small>NJ Ferraby 107 and 69 for Oxford,<br> AD Sears 5-73 (1st inns) for Cambridge</small>\n|-\n|[http://www.espncricinfo.com/series/18109/scorecard/833179/cambridge-university-vs-oxford-university-varsity-match-university-match-2015/ 170]\n|30 June 2015\n|Cambridge\n|bgcolor=\"#B7E1E4\"|Cambridge\n|5 wickets\n|<small>[[Matthew Hughes (cricketer)|MST Hughes]] 116 (2nd inns) for Oxford<br>AD Blofield 105 (1st inns), RJ Crichard 5-62 (1st inns), AR Patel 5-88 (2nd inns) for Cambridge<br>completed in three days</small>\n|-\n|[http://www.espncricinfo.com/series/8908/scorecard/985997/oxford-university-vs-cambridge-university-varsity-match-university-match-2016/ 171]\n|5 July 2016\n|Oxford\n|style=\"background:#004685; color:#FFFFFF\"|Oxford\n|103 runs\n|<small>[[Matthew Hughes (cricketer)|MST Hughes]] 116 (1st inns), [[Dan Escott|DA Escott]] 125 (2nd inns) & 6-71 (2nd inns), J Marsden 5-41 (1st inns) & 8-92 (match) for Oxford <br>AR Patel 5-86 (1st inns) for Cambridge </small>\n|-\n|[http://www.espncricinfo.com/series/18103/scorecard/1101753/cambridge-university-vs-oxford-university-varsity-match-university-match-2017/ 172]\n|4 July 2017\n|Cambridge\n|bgcolor=\"#B7E1E4\"|Cambridge\n|216 runs\n|<small>RJ Crichard 5-74 (1st inns) & 6-68 (2nd inns) for Cambridge</small>\n|-\n|[http://www.espncricinfo.com/series/18691/scorecard/1144954/oxford-university-vs-cambridge-university-varsity-match-university-match-2018/ 173]\n|2 July 2018\n|Oxford\n|style=\"background:#004685; color:#FFFFFF\"|Oxford\n|9 wickets\n|<small>[[Matthew Naylor|MA Naylor]] 202 (1st inns), [[Dan Escott|DA Escott]] 175 (1st inns), THS Pettman 5-41 (1st inns) & 8-113 (match) for Oxford</small>\n|-\n|[https://www.espncricinfo.com/series/19020/scorecard/1192570/cambridge-university-vs-oxford-university-varsity-match-university-match-2019 174]\n|2 July 2019\n|Cambridge\n|style=\"background:#004685; color:#FFFFFF\"|Oxford\n|8 wickets\n|<small>GT Hargrave 146 (1st inns), THS Pettman 5-19 (2nd inns) & 8-80 (match) for Oxford</small>\n|}\n\n=== Highest and lowest scores by each side ===\n*604    Cambridge University v Oxford University, The Parks, 2002\n*611-5d Oxford Un