istrikt Lublin 1939\u20131944 |date=2000 |publisher=[[Harrassowitz Verlag]] |location=Leipzig |isbn=978-3-447-05063-0 |ref=harv |language=de|trans-title=German Civil Administration and the Persecution of Jews in the General Government: a Case Study on the Lublin District 1939\u20131944}}\n*{{cite book |last1=Protassewicz |first1=Irena |title=A Polish Woman's Experience in World War II: Conflict, Deportation and Exile |date=2019 |publisher=[[Bloomsbury Publishing]] |location=New York |isbn=978-1-350-07993-9 |ref=harv |language=en}}\n*{{cite book |last1=Rice |first1=Monika |title=What! Still Alive?!: Jewish Survivors in Poland and Israel Remember Homecoming |date=2017 |publisher=[[Syracuse University Press]] |location=Syracuse |isbn=978-0-8156-5419-3 |ref=harv |language=en}}\n*{{cite book |last1=Rubin |first1=Arnon |title=The Kielce Pogrom\u2014Spontaneity, Provocation or Part of a Country-Wide Scheme? |date=2004 |publisher=Tel Aviv University Press |location=Tel Aviv |isbn=978-965-555-144-0 |series=Facts and Fictions about the Rescue of the Polish Jewry During the Holocaust |ref=harv |language=en|volume=6}}\n*{{cite book |last1=Rubin |first1=Arnon|entry=D\u0119blin\u2013Irena|title=District Lublin| series=The Rise and Fall of the Jewish Communities in Poland and their Relics Today|volume=2 |date=2006|orig-year=1999 |publisher=Tel Aviv University Press |location=Tel Aviv |isbn=978-965-90744-2-6 |ref=harv |pp=89\u201393}}\n*{{cite book |last1=Silberklang |first1=David |title=Gates of Tears: the Holocaust in the Lublin District |date=2013 |publisher=Yad Vashem |location=Jerusalem |isbn=978-965-308-464-3 |language=English|title-link=Gates of Tears: the Holocaust in the Lublin District |ref=harv}}\n*{{cite book |last1=Snyder |first1=Timothy D. |authorlink1=Timothy D. Snyder |title=Bloodlands: Europe Between Hitler and Stalin |date=2012 |publisher=[[Basic Books]] |location=New York |isbn=978-0-465-03297-6 |ref=harv |language=en|title-link=Bloodlands: Europe Between Hitler 